	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">lidnariq wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Removing the gloptops isn't hard (<a href="http://www.kevtris.org/Projects/votraxpss/unpot.html" class="postlink">kevtris explains</a>), but soldering a new ROM is going to be a Serious Endeavor, involving lots of rewiring and surface-mount work. I would look for something else, or buy one of INL's kits.</div><br />Of course, removing the glop tops from a cartridge using that method would destroy whatever was underneath them, since they're just bare silicon wafers bonded directly to the circuit board (with the glop tops there to protect the chips rather than prevent you from looking at them). If you wanted to somehow remove them intact, you'd need to use rather nasty chemicals (e.g. <em>boiling</em> fuming nitric acid).

		

		</td>
	</tr>
